2. cs.RO (Robotics) is also likely as the paper discusses the use of the proposed method in robotics applications. 
3. cs.LG (Machine Learning) is another likely category as the paper proposes a learning algorithm for generating binary descriptors. 
4. cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is a possible category as the paper proposes a method for improving the performance of AI systems in loop-closure detection and place recognition. 
5. cs.MM (Multimedia) is also a possible category as the paper deals with visual features and their use in multimedia applications.
